---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
---

<Layout title="Juan Ignacio">
  <main>
    <h1>Juan Ignacio Sánchez</h1>
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p class="instructions">
      Based in Montevideo, Uruguay, I bring over 9 years of experience
      specializing in Python, Django, and backend technologies. Recently, I’ve
      rekindled my passion for frontend development, diving into React, Next.js,
      and Astro to build modern, user-friendly interfaces. <br /><br />Feel free
      to explore 👉 to learn more about my professional journey, the tools I’ve
      mastered, and a little more about who I am!
    </p>

    <section id="experience">
      <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

      <div class="job">
        <h4>Limit Wholesale Brokers | May 2022 - Present</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Built and maintained integrations with 10+ third-party APIs using
            Python/Django.
          </li>
          <li>
            Established communication channels to effectively reduce unforeseen
            changes in external API integration.
          </li>
          <li>
            Collaborated with API consumers to improve incident response and
            reduce debugging clutter.
          </li>
          <li>
            Authored the integration with Trava Security to provide risk
            assessment reports.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <em
            >The interesting part of this project was finding common patterns
            among Carrier requirements to minimize users' burden.</em
          >
        </p>
        <p>
          <em
            >Integration tests were a pain point, solved by prioritizing the
            most valuable ones to balance quality and deadlines.</em
          >
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="job">
        <h4>Rootstrap | Jan 2020 - Jan 2022</h4>
        <p>
          At Rootstrap, I joined multiple teams across various projects.
          Highlights include:
        </p>
        <div class="project">
          <h4>Phylagen</h4>
          <p>
            Phylagen, a San Francisco-based biotech company, combines microbial
            genomics and data analytics to solve complex problems. I:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Built microservices from scratch using Django, HUG, Flask, and
              occasionally AWS Lambda.
            </li>
            <li>Integrated these microservices into a complex ETL pipeline.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="project">
          <h4>Sentry DashCam</h4>
          <p>
            The Sentry DashCam app & Wireless Bridge (Elon-1) enable Tesla
            owners to wirelessly view their Tesla Sentry alarm systems and
            manage DashCam videos. I:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Configured Raspberry Pi boards to act as USB gadgets collecting
              DVR data.
            </li>
            <li>
              Optimized video data using FFmpeg, enabling streaming capabilities
              via a REST API built with Flask.
            </li>
            <li>
              Automated server setup with bash scripting for easy user
              installation of pre-packaged system images.
            </li>
            <li>
              Handled limited Raspberry Pi computing power by optimizing FFmpeg
              using C/C++.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="job">
        <h4>Hipcam | Jun 2018 - Jan 2020</h4>
        <p>
          Hipcam, based in Buenos Aires, develops smart home security systems. I
          worked on:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Video processing services (on-demand clip generation with watermark
            and timestamps).
          </li>
          <li>User and camera tracking modules using Python/Django.</li>
          <li>
            Real-time camera data consumption modules using Python/Tornado.
          </li>
          <li>
            Maintaining the face-recognition microservice and contributing to
            infrastructure (AWS, DVR servers).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="job">
        <h4>Cilan | Jun 2014 - May 2018</h4>
        <p>
          At Cilan, an IT solutions company in Uruguay, I worked as a full-stack
          developer, specializing in:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Building applications using Django, Django Rest Framework, and
            KnockoutJS.
          </li>
          <li>Database management with PostgreSQL and MySQL.</li>
          <li>Providing services like VoIP and web development.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <ul role="list" class="link-card-grid">
      <Card
        href="https://github.com/juan-ignacio-sanchez/awstanding/"
        title="AWStanding"
        body="Python library that helps managing AWS Secrets."
      />
      <Card
        href="https://astro.build/integrations/"
        title="Integrations"
        body="Supercharge your project with new frameworks and libraries."
      />
      <Card
        href="https://astro.build/themes/"
        title="Themes"
        body="Explore a galaxy of community-built starter themes."
      />
      <Card
        href="https://astro.build/chat/"
        title="Community"
        body="Come say hi to our amazing Discord community. ❤️"
      />
    </ul>
  </main>

  <style>
    main {
      margin: auto;
      padding: 1rem;
      width: 800px;
      max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
      color: rgba(var(--accent-dark));
      font-size: 20px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .astro-a {
      position: absolute;
      top: -32px;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translatex(-50%);
      width: 220px;
      height: auto;
      z-index: -1;
    }
    .timespan {
      color: gray;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 4rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 0.5em;
    }
    h2,
    h3 {
      text-align: center;
    }
    .text-gradient {
      background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-size: 400%;
      background-position: 0%;
    }
    .instructions {
      color: rgba(var(--accent-dark));
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent-dark), 25%);
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 3px;
    }
    .instructions code {
      font-size: 0.8em;
      font-weight: bold;
      background: rgba(var(--accent-light), 12%);
      color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 0.3em 0.4em;
    }
    .instructions strong {
      color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
    }
    .link-card-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(24ch, 1fr));
      gap: 2rem;
      padding: 0;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
